  "content": {
    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a horizontal pole attached to a vertical wall by a pivot at point P. A ring is attached to the wall 1.2 meters above the pivot. Dashed lines are drawn from the ring to two points on the pole labeled Q and R. Point Q is located 0.6 meters from the wall, and point R is located 1.6 meters from the wall.\" src=\"/images/25600db6ca0862f3caf465d888ec90a8.svg\"></div></div></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A horizontal pole can rotate vertically about a pivot that is attached to a wall at Point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"P\"><math alttext=\"P\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>P</mtext></math></span></span>, as shown in the figure. A fixed ring is located higher up on the wall, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1.2\"><math alttext=\"1.2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1.2</mn></math></span></span> meters above the pivot, where a rope can be attached to support the pole. The figures show two possible attachment points on the pole for the rope, at points <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Q\"><math alttext=\"Q\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>Q</mtext></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"R\"><math alttext=\"R\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>R</mtext></math></span></span>. If the rope tension results in the same torque <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"tau sub 0\"><math alttext=\"tau sub 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>Ï„</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mstyle></math></span></span> for both attachment points, for which attachment point is the rope tension greater? What evidence supports reasoning for the claim?</p>\n",
    "answer": "i2",
    "choices": [
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Q\"><math alttext=\"Q\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>Q</mtext></math></span></span>. The rope is shorter when attached to Point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Q\"><math alttext=\"Q\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>Q</mtext></math></span></span>.</p>",
        "value": "i1"
